    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Bromley Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Ap. 4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Hooker</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have been confined to bed; otherwise I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. have written yesterday to have thanked you for your note about poor dear Henslow.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/> In two or three days do let me have literally one line. If he is well enough tell him how gratefully &amp; affectionately I shall love &amp; honour him to the day of my death.—</p>
<p>Ever yours | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Hooker’s letter has not been found. He was staying at the home of his father-in-law, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2235.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">John Stevens Henslow</ref>, who was seriously ill.</note>
        </div>        
            
